13:
That's what he told us, though we
have no proof of this. I recall that
you claimed this was Grey's home.
17:
Prika, are you prepared to accept
the truth we discover
here—whatever it may be?
23:
I'll be okay. I've got you guys here to
face it with me!
28:
So this is Grey's... place... It's about as
small as I imagined it to be.
30:
I told him I could make him a bigger,
nicer house, but he wouldn't have
any of it.
34:
These... are the letters I sent to my
prince.
38: Then Prince Frau really was Grey...
41: So it's true. He lied to me.
45: There has to be a reason.
48:
I just need to talk with him... And we
can figure this out, can't we?
51:
If that is an option, then it's definitely
one worth taking.
61:
Maybe it's one that never got sent
out to me?
65:
What's wrong, Alk? Let me see it
already!
69:
Prika... I need you to take a deep
breath, and maybe like sit down in
your castle before you read this—
72:
What? Now I'm even more curious
what's written inside!
77:
You should know, it's not a normal
letter—it's got a will, too.
83:
The world outside is so quiet from
here. It almost feels like nothing's
changed...
87:
No more visits, no more letters...
That's it.
93:
Why do people die anyways? What's
the point of death?
97:
Wh-whoa, what are you doing,
Stella?! We're not outside anymore.
You don't have to stick so close.
100:
People can remain by each other's
side, even without a reason.
104:
I guess that's true. Grey used to
stand next to me too, and...
106:
I just can't wrap my head around
the fact that I'll never see him again.
115:
You know, Grey said sorry for lying to
me...
121:
Yeah. Simon was right. I'm a
weapon, not a princess.
124: But Grey gave me a fake life.
132:
Fake or not, you're still here. Real.
Because I can touch you if I wanted
to.
138:
That's another thing gone with
death. I'll never be able to hug him
again.
141: Grey meant a lot to you.
147:
My entire life was these walls, these
poppets, the prince's letters—
153:
What's wrong? What are you
zooming around for?
160:
What is going on?! Are Prika and
Stella okay?
164:
They should both be in the castle
still. Whether they're safe or not is up
in the air, but we have to hold this
position!
168:
Keep it together, Alk! You cannot
afford to slip up now!
172:
How kind of you all to return... It
saves me the trouble of having to
hunt you down.
177:
Simon! What is the meaning of this?
What do you want with us?
180:
If you must know, I'm here to finish
what my father couldn't.
184: Your father? Do you mean... Grey?
188:
He devoted his entire life to
watching over a weapon that was
supposed to be disposed of and
forgotten...
190:
Protecting the bloodline that
destroyed our country. What a
waste of his life.
193:
Come again? Wasn't Mosnia
destroyed by civil war?
198:
It was. And the main cause of
destruction was the creation magic
of HER bloodline.
201:
Three hundred years ago there was
a thriving country here, and now
nothing is left.
203:
WE have nothing left. What meaning
is there in living?
205:
Her existence is a curse, and it is my
right to end it!
209:
I know the princess is inside. This
time, I won't fail...
